# Control: a COMPLETE multi-disc set must add no fetch work to the launch path — the
# one --check-rom (offline, manifest census) answers complete=1, so no
# --fetch-next-disc, no --download (only the ordinary saves probe runs).
desc fetch hook (lodor#7): --check-rom complete -> no disc fetch at all
invoke prehook
config paired
romarg Roms/PlayStation (PS)/✓ FF7.m3u
sdtext Roms/PlayStation (PS)/✓ FF7.m3u	FF7/D1.chd\nFF7/D2.chd\n
sdfile+ Roms/PlayStation (PS)/FF7/D1.chd
sdfile+ Roms/PlayStation (PS)/FF7/D2.chd
engine 0|RESULT complete=1 discs_total=2 discs_present=2
engine 0|
expect_exit 0
expect_trace ENGINE --check-rom
expect_trace_absent ENGINE --fetch-next-disc
expect_trace_absent ENGINE --download
